		<item>
		<title>What’s new with you – no, really</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/48Days/~3/9wLs8TKow6s/</link>

		<comments>http://www.48days.com/2011/05/24/what%e2%80%99s-new-with-you-%e2%80%93-no-really/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 24 May 2011 08:00:16 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Dan Miller</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Finding Passion]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[No More Mondays]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Personal Development]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[franklin]]></category>

		<category><![CDATA[grant achatz]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[next]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[nissan]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.48days.com/?p=7051</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Here in Franklin, TN we have an abundance of restaurants.  The Tennessean says there are 150 lunch restaurants within a one mile radius of the new <a href="http://www.nissanusa.com/about/corporate-info/nissan-in-north-america.html">North American Nissan corporate headquarters</a> here.
So how do you stand out in a sea of sameness – where there are many places to get sushi, a salad or burrito? <a rel="attachment wp-att-7052" href="http://www.48days.com/2011/05/24/what%e2%80%99s-new-with-you-%e2%80%93-no-really/leisure-suit/"></a>&#8230; <a href="http://www.48days.com/2011/05/24/what%e2%80%99s-new-with-you-%e2%80%93-no-really/" class="read_more">More...</a>]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Here in Franklin, TN we have an abundance of restaurants.  The Tennessean says there are 150 lunch restaurants within a one mile radius of the new <a href="http://www.nissanusa.com/about/corporate-info/nissan-in-north-america.html">North American Nissan corporate headquarters</a> here.</p>
<p>So how do you stand out in a sea of sameness – where there are many places to get sushi, a salad or burrito? <a rel="attachment wp-att-7052" href="http://www.48days.com/2011/05/24/what%e2%80%99s-new-with-you-%e2%80%93-no-really/leisure-suit/"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-7052" title="leisure suit" src="http://www.48days.com/wp-content/uploads/leisure-suit-300x276.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="276" /></a> Joanne and I frequent lots of these places and quickly decide if we like that particular ambience and menu.  How can they draw us back if we don’t like Thai food?</p>
<p>On April 1<sup>st</sup>, famous chef <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grant_Achatz">Grant Achatz</a> opened his new restaurant, <a href="https://www.nextrestaurant.com/website/faq">Next</a>, in Chicago.  Every three months, the restaurant is going to abandon its entire menu and start over.  Currently on the menu is Potage à la Tortue Claire – yep that’s a clear turtle soup with fennel, leek, parsley, and carrots.  If that’s not your fancy, you may look forward to the mignardises.</p>
<p>The point is – what are you doing to freshen up what you offer.   Whether that’s a twist on the products you’re known for or an added area of expertise on your resume, chances are a stagnant “menu” of what you offer will diminish in appeal.</p>
<p>Maybe it&#8217;s time to trade in that <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leisure_suit">leisure suit</a> you wore to the prom.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
